<br>
It was suggest above that since PoP IS so much different than other content (which I still don't see how anyone can dispute), that we consider another form of alliance.  In this alliance, when two guilds team up to kill a PoP mob, they form a POP ALLIANCE that condemns them to share all POP CONTENT in the future, but leaves the rest of the game on normal, rotational, single-entity rules.<br>
<br>
Since PoP IS different, I believe that this is something to at least CONSIDER.  There IS a compromise here too.  The teamers are willing to sacrifice the ability to be seperate entities on any and all PoP mobs in exchange for being able to team on boss mobs are a dual guild entity.<br>
<br>
I already see the arguements that are about to pop up, bt go ahead anyway, lets see what everyone has to say about this.<br>
