</span><br>  Posts: 468<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/23/03 7:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=646.topic&index=442>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Response to Teamwork thread in guild rep forum.</span><hr size=1> Okay Josephian,<br>
<br>
You bring up some good points that I knew would need to be addressed sooner or later.<br>
<br>
1.  SoY is about the same size as BotS:<br>
<br>
Well, this is *technically* true I guess.  But you are right, it is the play styles of the guilds that make them different.<br>
<br>
There are 20 or less &quot;BotS-Style Hardcore&quot; players in SoY, which gives us 20 + &lt;insert random number here&gt; players on each night with which to raid.  I assume that these numbers are similar with other guilds that are in our similar position.  So in order for us to take on mobs like AD, we would need TWO guilds of our size both having a decent night (say 40 members apiece) in order to make a raid cap.  <br>
<br>
Now I'm not saying that the raid HAS TO HAVE 72 people in it, but there is barely a shot in the dark's chance that SoY will have 55-60 people on in one night to try a new mob.  This happens maybe twice a year.<br>
<br>
Now, I know what you are going to say: &quot;Well thats not our problem, recruit a different kind of player&quot; or whatever.  Well, why?  We like the kind of player we have in our own little click.  What I have seen suggested in the last 10 posts is that because we choose to play this way we should be excluded from content on that basis.  I'm trying to come up with a way that we will get to see content in this game that doesn't rip apart the fabric of system, but lets me experience what I paid for.<br>
<br>
Look guys, the issues isn't that our guilds are not capable of experiencing PoP content like alot of you are making it out to be.  The issue is that we aren't capable of experiencing it in the SAME WAY that the &quot;ubers&quot; are.  We don't have the dedicated players, the gear, etc.  <br>
<br>
Well I bet you a dollar that Verant didn't think of CH rotations until players starting using them.  I know for a fact, being an ex-guide, that they didn't think of Camping or Pulling when they designed the game.  In the same respect, I feel like its possible for me to be able to kill Vindi in a different way than BotS does, because that is the way I have to do it to get it done.<br>
<br>
2.  This &quot;discrepancy&quot; that you are pointing out isn't so strange when you stop to think about it.  I don't know about other people that where fighting on the pro-team side, but I have moved on the from the whole &quot;these mobs aren't rotation mobs thing&quot;.  So naturally, I am assuming all of the mobs ARE rotation mobs even though they aren't on the page.<br>
<br>
I'm doing this because in these eyes of the &quot;ubers&quot; and people with the &quot;spirit of the rathe&quot; in their hearts, they see two allied guilds killing AD to be just as offensive as two allied guilds killing Rallos Zek.<br>
<br>
Therefore, I'm trying to come up with something that will allow us less experienced and equipped guilds (is that better?) to be able to see some content that we would otherwise be years from seeing yet.<br>
<br>
3.  This has nothing to do with your response Josephian, but I need to mention it in this post.<br>
<br>
There are some seriously faulty thoughts in this thread.<br>
<br>
I think the biggest &quot;concern&quot; that has been raised so far is the illegitimate killing of Rallos Zek by a &quot;rogue&quot; guild.  <br>
<br>
Well...here's a problem.  If the reward for killing Rallos Zek is SO GREAT, that a massive Zerging by an alliance can get 72 people flagged (assuming they EVER get lucky enough to kill RZ) at a time, that negates the need to do the VT timesinks.<br>
<br>
I haven't started farming ore, shards, killing emp.  Do you think I want to do that if I don't have to (I'm not saying ME, I&quot;m just using myself as an example)?  Hell no...so there is the problem...people might be able to skip content with some seriously messed up luck and enough people.  My god...that would be horrid.  <br>
<br>
If I was a Post-VT guild would that piss me off?  Hell yes it would piss me off, but maybe not for the reason some of you might think.  Initially I think it would piss me off because people didn't have to waste all the time I wasted, but no, thats not the big picture.<br>
<br>
The big picture is that two guilds full of people with mediocre play styles and horrible gear just entered a set of zones (elemental planes) that they should not be in with their set of people and gear.  They will have to fight for their life just to kill a named and they are trying to split elemental armor drops between their massive 300 people zerg force.  It will be chaos...they will grow to hate each other, and they will split up.  <br>
<br>
Then...we will have two or three smaller guilds with people running around in planes that they have NO BUSINESS being in, and they will be getting their asses waxed, botching spawns, ruining trials and events, and getting in the way of the people who are actually ready for the content.<br>
<br>
They will STILL have to either go back to VT (doing the long timesinks and farming) or wait around for the same amount of time praying and playing roulette for the hope of an elemental armor drop.<br>
<br>
More likely they will try to quit their guild and join other guilds that actually have the capability to move on.  But wait, those guilds HATE THEM now, because they have been fucking up their shit for the past 3 or 4 months TRYING to play-play with content they weren't ready for.  They caused the uber guilds alot of headaches and missed mobs, and the ubers aren't interested in having any of this trash in their guild.<br>
<br>
Holy shit...I just talked me self out of this.  Fuck alliances.<br>
<br>
