Just reread this one from a few pages back, but it strikes me as still the current attitude of the anti &quot;do it yourself or become an official alliance&quot; camp</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
AD, Grummus, and Behemoth are NOT ****CURRENTLY**** rotation mobs and thus can be teamed until people are blue in the face.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sure keep threatening I like that.  In fact all people like being threatened.  There is nothing you can do if &quot;we&quot; decide to do it so NA NA NA BOO BOO.  Here's a threat... or rather a reality.  Look to some of the other servers where the current 2-3 elemental guilds perma gank certain flag mobs to cockblock ANY other guilds from getting in.  At least on this server when you get to RZ I can pretty much bet you'll be given an unhampered shot rather than being steam rolled as an &quot;UBER&quot; guild goes right past you and ganks him right out from under you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
It is paranoia due to people assuming that because the Elemental Planes offer so much, that guilds will start teaming up to kill Rallos Zek and the like. I haven't heard any intentions of this and I do not foresee this. If a guild were to do this, it would, indeed, be a server first and stray from definate norms of the Rathe. If you don't want people making assumptions that you are just greedy and want to keep the exp zones to yourselves, then don't assume that the rest of the server is greedy and will end up teaming up on a mob like RZ. Afterall, this was a one time deal and the intentions were well laid out going in.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yup that is what this was about on &quot;other&quot; side of the fence.  At least that is what it was a page or two ago.  Now it is about entitelement to be in the elemental planes no matter how you get there.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
What I have seen suggested in the last 10 posts is that because we choose to play this way we should be excluded from content on that basis. I'm trying to come up with a way that we will get to see content in this game that doesn't rip apart the fabric of system, but lets me experience what I paid for.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sure you'll scream bloody blue murder everytime TL/NB/BotS steam rolls you on a flag mob that your <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>*non alliance team*</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is going for.  However it is ok to &quot;stick&quot; it to them as far as giving a &quot;fair&quot; shot based on how you see fair as being.  Which is it, do you want &quot;uber&quot; guilds perma killing flag mobs to cockblock you or do you want fair and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>equal</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> shots at them?  People seem to want it both ways.  Don't cockblock us, don't kill our old world rotation mobs, but we want to take on new high end content however we want regardless of how anyone else feels about it.  You want the blessing to team it all the way up, none of the penalties associated with alliances in the rotations PLUS you don't want to be cockblocked.  If that isn't wanting your cake and eating it too, I can't think of anything that would be.<br>
<br>
Tell me what is it you proposing to give up again?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
It was suggest above that since PoP IS so much different than other content (which I still don't see how anyone can dispute), that we consider another form of alliance.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
AND I suggest you either shit or get off the pot.  Either make an alliance or don't make an alliance, but stop trying to take as much as you can without conceding anything.  So far all I have seen is ways to rationalize that it is ok to have you Trak/Sev spawn protected AND get it as many times as possible, PLUS get as many high end mobs as well.  Until that changes you won't see much movement on the other side either.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
The reason we do NOT band together is not for GREED, and trying to be on individual rotations as you are trying to suggest. The reason is because the people in two mid-sized guilds are usually quite different breeds of people.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
