Yep last time Gore popped 3 of our members killed Gore about 3 weeks ago.  I can see how this is relevant because 3 people can kill AD.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
So don't blow smoke about how it hurts the high end guilds because if its on rotation you have been farming it for months before any of the mid size guilds get thier.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And don't blow smoke about how much it hurts smaller guilds.  Coming from all ends of the spectrums I was always thankful that BotS, TL, NB, FK, SoT wasn't going around ganking my guilds Trak spawn when I was in a smaller guild.  It doesn't take them a full guild and 12 hours to kill Trak. <br>
<br>
The fact of the matter is I see this as benfitting mid size guilds the most and harming small guilds the most.  Guilds that are on barely one or two rotations should not have to share 10 rotation slots with mid sized guilds that have decided to team up for high end content.  Look &quot;backwards&quot; to the guilds coming up behind you and see how fair it is to them to be sharing 10 rotation slots with mid sized guilds that are also teaming to kill high end content.  From their perspective all they can see is that you guys are getting 10 rotation slots on the mobs they want access to, PLUS the 10 mid sized guilds are forming various &quot;teams&quot; to kill AD for comparable VT loot to have to avoid going there.  How can that possibly be fair to them?  How are you sharing with them?<br>
